<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910419-0111</DOCNO><DOCID>910419-0111.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- UST Inc.:   Net Income Advanced 13%   During the First Quarter</HL><DATE>04/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7D</SO><CO>   UST</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)CONSUMER AND HOUSEHOLD PRODUCTS AND SERVICES (HOU)CONSUMER AND HOUSEHOLD PRODUCTS (HPR)TOBACCO PRODUCTS (TOB)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)</RE><LP>   UST Inc. reported a 13% increase in first-quarter netincome to $59.3 million on a sales gain of 16%.   The Greenwich, Conn., tobacco and wine concern earned 52cents a share in the latest period. In the year-ago quarter,the company had profit of $52.6 million, or 46 cents a share,which included a $3 million pretax gain from the earlytermination of a licensing agreement. Sales rose to $203.4million from $175.3 million.</LP><TEXT>   The company said its tobacco segment benefited fromincreased sales of moist smokeless tobacco in the latestperiod.</TEXT></DOC>